---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Services — Kenius" description="What Kenius does: AI strategy & consulting first, then custom development — agents, conversational & voice AI, document automation, copilots and integration." path="/services">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="breadcrumb reveal"><a href="/">Kenius</a> — Services</div>
        <h1 class="reveal" data-d="1">We advise first, then <span class="it mark">build what fits.</span></h1>
        <p class="lead reveal" data-d="2">Kenius is a consultancy, not a product. We start by understanding your business and recommending what’s actually worth doing — then design and build it as a custom solution.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="padding-top:0">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="detail reveal" id="consulting">
          <div><div class="d-num">01</div><div class="cap" style="margin-top:1rem">Start here</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2>AI strategy &amp; consulting</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Before anyone writes a line of code, we work out where AI helps you — and where it doesn’t. You get a clear, costed plan you can act on, with us or without us.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>Workflow &amp; opportunity mapping</span></li>
              <li><span>Feasibility &amp; ROI estimates</span></li>
              <li><span>A prioritised roadmap</span></li>
              <li><span>Build / buy / don’t recommendations</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="agents">
          <div><div class="d-num">02</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2>Custom AI agents &amp; automation</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Bespoke agents that complete whole tasks across your tools — they plan, act, and ask a human before anything risky. Built around your real workflow, not a template.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>Plans a task before touching anything</span></li>
              <li><span>Scoped access to only the tools you grant</span></li>
              <li><span>Human approval on the consequential steps</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="voice">
          <div><div class="d-num">03</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2>Conversational &amp; voice AI</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Chat and phone assistants trained on your docs and policies — they listen (speech-to-text), speak (text-to-speech), and get things booked, 24/7, in a voice you approve.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>Book &amp; confirm appointments</span></li>
              <li><span>Answer FAQs &amp; route callers</span></li>
              <li><span>Take messages &amp; call back</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="automation">
          <div><div class="d-num">04</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2>Document &amp; process automation</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">Reading paperwork and typing it into systems is exactly what AI is best at. Invoices, forms, receipts — read, extracted, entered and reconciled, with exceptions flagged.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>Turn a PDF inbox into clean records</span></li>
              <li><span>Match, reconcile and post automatically</span></li>
              <li><span>Flag only the odd ones for a human</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="copilots">
          <div><div class="d-num">05</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2>Custom copilots &amp; knowledge</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">An assistant grounded in your company’s own knowledge — playbooks, history, policies — living inside the tools your team already uses.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>Answers grounded in your stuff, not the open internet</span></li>
              <li><span>Drafts in your voice, in seconds</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="detail reveal" id="integrations">
          <div><div class="d-num">06</div></div>
          <div>
            <h2>Integration &amp; data</h2>
            <p class="d-lead">The unglamorous part that makes everything work: connecting your systems safely, with scoped permissions, and getting your data into shape so AI can act on it.</p>
            <ul class="checks">
              <li><span>No rip-and-replace — keep the tools you like</span></li>
              <li><span>If it has an API, we can connect it</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section dark">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="cap reveal">Working together</span>
        <p class="big-statement reveal" data-d="1" style="margin-top:1.4rem">Three ways to <span class="it">start.</span></p>
        <div class="list" style="margin-top:clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem);border-color:var(--dark-line)">
          <div class="list-row reveal" style="border-color:var(--dark-line)">
            <span class="ln" style="color:var(--accent-dark)">/ Start here</span>
            <h3 style="color:var(--dark-text)">Assessment &amp; roadmap</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--dark-muted)">One to two weeks. We map your workflows and hand you a costed, prioritised plan — no obligation to build with us.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="list-row reveal" style="border-color:var(--dark-line)">
            <span class="ln" style="color:var(--accent-dark)">/ Most popular</span>
            <h3 style="color:var(--dark-text)">Build a pilot</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--dark-muted)">One use case, one fixed price, four to eight weeks. We build the real thing on your data and prove the value before you commit to more.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="list-row reveal" style="border-color:var(--dark-line)">
            <span class="ln" style="color:var(--accent-dark)">/ Ongoing</span>
            <h3 style="color:var(--dark-text)">Build, run &amp; support</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--dark-muted)">We build, look after and expand your solutions over time — or work alongside your team and hand over the keys.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">
        <h2 class="reveal" style="font-size:var(--t-h2);max-width:16ch">Not sure which one fits?</h2>
        <p class="reveal" data-d="1" style="margin-top:1.6rem;max-width:42ch">Tell us what your team does all day. We’ll point at the one thing worth doing first — even if it’s not us who should do it.</p>
        <p class="reveal" data-d="1" style="margin-top:2rem"><a class="tlink" href="/contact">Book a discovery call <span class="ar" aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a></p>
      </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
